@startuml algorithm_flow

title Queue Generation Pipeline (Stateless Functions)

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam BoxPadding 10

|Input|
start
:QueueInput JSON;
note right
  parameters:
    technology, instrument
    sampler, queue_pattern
    date, user, polarity
    **method: {pos: ..., neg: ...}**
    qc_frequency_override
  sample_groups:
    [{container_id, samples: [...]}]
end note

|Pipeline|

:1. validate_input();
note right
  **Input:** QueueInput, ConfigBundle
  **Output:** ValidatedInput
  ----
  • Check (instrument, sampler) combo
  • Resolve pattern config
  • Resolve QC layout
  • Resolve output format
end note

:2. build_queue_structure();
note right
  **Input:** num_samples, QueuePattern
  **Output:** list[str]
  ----
  Pure slot interleaving:
  ["QC03dia", "QC01", "default",
   "default", "clean", "QC01", ...]
end note

:3. generate_positions();
note right
  **Input:** num_samples, sampler_config
  **Output:** list[str]
  ----
  Vanquish: ["Y:A1", "Y:A2", ...]
  QC positions from qc_layouts.toml
end note

if (requires polarity?) then (metabolomics/lipidomics)
  :4. expand_polarities();
  note right
    **Input:** structure, ["pos", "neg"]
    **Output:** [(slot, polarity), ...]
    ----
    Duplicate each slot per polarity
  end note
else (proteomics)
  :4. no expansion;
  note right
    [(slot, None), ...]
  end note
endif

:5. populate_rows();
note right
  **Input:**
    expanded_structure
    user_samples (B-Fabric)
    positions, qc_layout
    samples_config
    params.method: {pos: ..., neg: ...}
  **Output:** list[QueueRow]
  ----
  For each (sample_id, polarity):
  • Get sample definition
  • Assign position
  • Format file_name
  • Get method[polarity] -> path
  • Format data_path
end note

:6. format_output();
note right
  **Input:** rows, OutputFormat
  **Output:** CSV string
  ----
  Map internal fields to
  output columns via
  output_formats.toml
end note

|Output|
:Queue CSV file;
note right
  xcalibur: .csv
  chronos: .csv
  hystar: .csv
end note

stop

legend right
  |= Symbol |= Meaning |
  | validate_input | Config validation + resolution |
  | build_queue_structure | Pure QC interleaving |
  | generate_positions | Stateless position generation |
  | expand_polarities | Polarity duplication |
  | populate_rows | Fill all row data |
  | format_output | Column mapping to CSV |
endlegend

@enduml
